story.title: The Love Questions - Episode 3

messages.text: Sera is waiting outside the karaoke bar‚Ä¶
When some guys start hassling her.
They tease her about waiting all alone and goad her to go home with them.
Suddenly, Christian comes running out from inside the bar.
Hey. HEY! You guys think it‚Äôs okay to talk to a girl like that?
You creeps better get OUT of here.
Christian! Wow, you look JUST like your profile.
Guys who say dirty stuff to girls.
It‚Äôs part of being in the big city ‚Äî
I‚Äôve handled myself okay so far.
Lucky you look like your profile picture.
Otherwise I might have thought you were some crazy weirdo.
You look like your picture too ‚Äî
I‚Äôm just your average science girl.
Then why is every guy on the street staring at you?
Because this dress is bright yellow.
I got here an hour early.
Yeah. Didn‚Äôt want to miss you.
This way ‚Äî it‚Äôs on the first floor.
Thank goodness! If you‚Äôd have made me walk five flights of stairs‚Ä¶
Wow, you‚Äôre holding the door for me!
I‚Äôve never seen so much glass in one place.
All the better to see the view, right?
Times Square looks fantastic from this height.
Here ‚Äî I reserved us a table.
You must have been here REALLY early to get this one.
Yeah, I‚Äôve been here a while.
Ooh, and the cocktails look FUN!
So what kind of music do you like?
How can you be not sure?
I haven‚Äôt thought about music in a while.
I guess I like those old-fashioned love songs from the 1950s.
I really love Unchained Melody by the Righteous Brothers.
But the excitement in Christian‚Äôs face disappears‚Ä¶
When he sees the sadness in Sera‚Äôs eyes
He puts his hand on her arm.
Thinking about that song is hard.
It makes me remember when we were all together.
You know, it makes me think of my brother.
He used to play it over and over.
Look at us ‚Äî lost in our memories.
It‚Äôs good to sit in silence sometimes.
I guess I‚Äôd have to agree with that.
Maybe Unchained Melody should be OUR song instead.
The words kind of fit with us, don‚Äôt you think?
That‚Äôs how I‚Äôve felt this entire week.
Hey, don‚Äôt go all shy on me.
So are you going to sing me a song, rock star?
Hey man? Can you hook up some Elvis Presley?
Let me just check this mic.
For the first time, Sera lets the words overwhelm her ‚Äî
She feels tears prickle in her eyes.
Wow, nice singing. You‚Äôre really good. Your voice is‚Ä¶
You put so much feeling into it.
Thanks. I guess I‚Äôve had a lot of practice.
My band has been together for a while.
So what are you going to sing next?
I reckon it‚Äôs time for a duet.
Is there something you‚Äôve always wanted to do, but have never done?
I need my next cocktail before I answer that one.
Waiter? Two more cocktails and two shots of tequila.
So tell me what YOU‚ÄôVE always wanted to do first.
I‚Äôve always wanted to climb Mount Washington.
Ugh! That was a STRONG shot!
I thought it tasted pretty good.
Okay ‚Äî I need another one if I‚Äôm gonna sing.
I don‚Äôt want to be accused of getting you drunk.
So why do you want to climb Mount Washington?
I‚Äôm not answering that yet. Not until‚Ä¶
Drink your cocktail and grab the mike.
It can‚Äôt be any scarier than that apartment fire.
Get ready ‚Äî it‚Äôs a short intro.
How can I sing with you?
And then the pair looks into each other‚Äôs eyes.
Come on‚Ä¶join in for the chorus.
Sera joins in, stumbling over the words at first.
She laughs nervously, but then she meets Christian‚Äôs gaze again.
And the music takes over ‚Äî the pair sings together.
I did it! I sang the whole song!
I loved hearing you do it.
You just need to let go more.
I‚Äôm impressed ‚Äî you conquered your fears!
All it took was two cocktails and a shot of tequila‚Ä¶
Anyway, weren‚Äôt you going to tell me why you want to climb Mount Washington?
Yeah. It‚Äôs because of my brother, the one who died five years ago.
Oh‚Ä¶I don‚Äôt want to make you talk about him if you don‚Äôt want to.
No, I want to. I like remembering him.
He wanted to join the army‚Ä¶
But they wouldn‚Äôt let him in.
So he decided to prove he was manly enough, then reapply.
He and a buddy climbed Mount Washington.
And Leo got swept up in it.
But I know he‚Äôs up there somewhere.
I‚Äôve always wanted to climb that mountain.
Sera looks Christian in the eye. Below their gaze‚Ä¶
Listen, I hope you get to say your goodbye.
If I tell more sad stories, will you keep holding my hand?
Yeah, I guess it‚Äôs not all that funny.
What have you always wanted to do, but have never done?
